<Base title="Homekeep — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 7, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Homekeep collects nothing. Your home maintenance tasks stay on your device.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Maintenance tasks, schedules, completion history, and app settings are stored locally on
     your device. Your data never touches our servers, because we don't have any.</p>

  <h2>Notifications</h2>
  <p>With your permission, Homekeep schedules maintenance reminders as local notifications on
     your device. Nothing about them ever leaves it. You can revoke notification access at any
     time in system Settings.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No accounts. No analytics. No ads. No third-party SDKs. No tracking of any kind.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Email us at <a href="mailto:support@sunpebblelabs.com">support@sunpebblelabs.com</a>.</p>
</Base>
